<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="ru">
<head>
	<meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

	<title>Avecode</title>


	<link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/style.css">
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.0/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-9aIt2nRpC12Uk9gS9baDl411NQApFmC26EwAOH8WgZl5MYYxFfc+NcPb1dKGj7Sk" crossorigin="anonymous">
	<script src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.0/js/bootstrap.min.js" integrity="sha384-OgVRvuATP1z7JjHLkuOU7Xw704+h835Lr+6QL9UvYjZE3Ipu6Tp75j7Bh/kR0JKI" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>

</head>
<body>
	<div class="container head-block">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="head col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-6">
			<div class="head__title align-self-center">
				<h1>Welcome to <span class="green-text">Avecode</span></h1>
				<div class="head__subtitle">
					<p>Folow this sample design to learn everything you need to know to use Avocode properly.</p>
				</div>	
			</div>
			</div>
			<div class="head-logo col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-6 text-center">
				<img src="assets/img/5-layers.png" alt="Avecode">
			</div>	
		</div>
			
	</div>

	<div class="divider container"><hr></div>

	<div class="container text-center">
		<div class="title">
			Basics of the Avocode App
		</div>
		<div class="subtitle">
			<p>Avocode UI is split into three main sections. A panel on the left, a large canvas to preview your designs in the middle, and inspector panel on the right for details about selected layers.</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="container">
		<div class="UI-img">
			<img src="assets/img/UI.png" alt="UI">
		</div>
	</div>	

	<div class="container">
		<div class="row justify-content-center">
			<div class="item">
				<div class="row">
					<div class="item__icon">
						<img src="assets/img/2-layers.png" alt="Red">
					</div>
					<div class="text">
						<div class="item__title">
							Layers
						</div>
						<div class="item__subtitle">
							Select any layer to export it, or to get web & mobile code, sizes..
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="item">
				<div class="row">
					<div class="item__icon">
						<img src="assets/img/2-layers-versions.png" alt="Yellow">
					</div>
					<div class="text">
						<div class="item__title">
							Versions
						</div>
						<div class="item__subtitle">
							Keep track of design versions to avoid conflicts.
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="item">
				<div class="row">
					<div class="item__icon">
						<img src="assets/img/2-layers-info.png" alt="Red">
					</div>
					<div class="text">
						<div class="item__title">
							Info
						</div>
						<div class="item__subtitle">
							See details of the design including the list of all fonts.
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="black-bg container-fluid">
		<div class="container black-bg-container">
			<div class="row align-items-center black-bg-row">
				<div class="col black-bg-item">
					<div class="black-bg__title">
						Get code from layer styles
					</div>
					<div class="black-bg__subtitle">
						Export CSS, Swift, Android & React Native code from the Styles panel on your right.
					</div>
					<div class="black-bg__tip">
						FOR EXAMPLE, TRY THE BUTTON BELOW
					</div>
					<div class="black-bg__button">
						<a href="#" class="btn">click me</a>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="col black-bg-item">
					<img src="assets/img/Styles_Bitmap.png" alt="">
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="container text-center">
		<div class="figures">
			<img src="assets/img/figures.png" alt="Figures">
		</div>
		<div class="title">
			Use the Ruler tool to measure distances
		</div>
		<div class="subtitle">
			Just hold <span><img src="assets/img/alt-button.png" alt="Alt Button"></span> to start using the Ruler tool.
		</div>
		<div class="inspect-screen">
			<img src="assets/img/inspect-screen.png" alt="Inspector Screen">
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="grey-bg container-fluid">
		<div class="container grey-bg-container">
			<div class="row grey-bg-row align-items-center">
				<div class="col">
					<img src="assets/img/grey-bg-img.png" alt="Image">
				</div>
				<div class="col">
					<div class="title">
						Select any layer and hit “<span class="green-text">Export</span>”
					</div>
					<div class="subtitle">
						Choose if you want to export PNG, JPEG, SVG, or WebP.
					</div>
					<div class="subtitle">
						You can also export the assets in various sizes for iOS and Android like @2x, @3x, xhdpi, etc.
					</div>
					<div class="subtitle">
						<span class="green-text">Tip:</span> You can select more layers at once by holding
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="w-100"></div>
				<div class="grey-bg__item">
					<div class="grey-bg__icon">
						<img src="assets/img/kokoro.png" alt="Kokoro">
					</div>
					<div class="grey-bg__iconTitle">
						Export as one SVG image
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="grey-bg__item">
					<div class="grey-bg__icon">
						<img src="assets/img/triangle.png" alt="Triangle">
					</div>
					<div class="grey-bg__iconTitle">
						Export as one merged JPEG image in @1x
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="grey-bg__item">
					<div class="grey-bg__icon">
						<img src="assets/img/belly.png" alt="Belly">
					</div>
					<div class="grey-bg__iconTitle">
						Export as separate PNGs in @1x and @2x
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>			
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="black-bg black-bg-2 container-fluid">
		<div class="container">
			<br><br><br><br>
			<div class="black-bg__title mt">
			Use the Color picker tool to inspect colors
			</div>
			<div class="black-bg__subtitle">
				Just press <span><img src="assets/img/i-button.png" alt="I Buttin"></span> to start using the Color picker.
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="container">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-6">
					<img src="assets/img/smile.png" alt="Smile">
				</div>
				<div class="col-6">
					<img src="assets/img/color-pallet.png" alt="Color Pallet">
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="margin-8"></div>
	<div class="container text-center ">
		<div class="title">
			Copy this text to your clipboard.
		</div>
		<div class="subtitle">
			<p><span class="green-text">Double click the text</span>, or just select it and press <span><img src="assets/img/cmd-button.png" alt=""></span> to copy.</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="divider container"><hr></div>
	<div class="margin-8"></div>
	<div class="container">
		<div class="row ">
			<div class="col-6 big-text align-self-center">
				Now it’s time to add your own design
			</div>
			<div class="col-6">
				<img src="assets/img/drag-image.png" alt="Drag and Drop">
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="margin-8"></div>

	<footer>
		4e kalai verstka?
	</footer>


    <!-- jQuery (necessary for Bootstrap's JavaScript plugins) -->
    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.3/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <!-- Include all compiled plugins (below), or include individual files as needed -->
    <script src="assets/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>